torrentkino (0.11) wheezy; urgency=low

  * IPV4 support including NSS and multicast
  * Leave multicast group at the end
  * Only send an announce success when actually being successful. (Limits)

 -- Aiko Barz <aiko@chroot.de>  Sun, 20 Oct 2013 23:06:00 +0100
torrentkino (0.10) wheezy; urgency=low

  * Renamed masala to torrentkino.
  * Merged tumbleweed into torrentkino.
  * Switched to Linus Torvalds SHA1 implementation.
  * AES support is off by default. Needs PolarSSL. See Makefile.
  * ARM support. Tested on Raspbian/Raspberry PI.
  * Ignore link-local polution.
  * Use info_hash database for lookups too for 2 node only swarms.
  * Better startup timings for 2 node only swarms.

 -- Aiko Barz <aiko@chroot.de>  Mon, 10 Oct 2013 23:32:00 +0100
torrentkino (0.9) wheezy; urgency=low

  * Use a sorted list for get_peers searches instead of bucket containers to save some bytes.
  * By default, be verbose in the console and quiet while running as a daemon.

 -- Aiko Barz <aiko@chroot.de>  Mon, 16 Sep 2013 23:25:00 +0100
torrentkino (0.8) wheezy; urgency=low

  * Limit the number of info_hashes, that can be stored.
  * Limit the number of nodes, that can be stored per info_hash.
  * Return NULL bytes as the token if the info_hash DB grows beyond all limits.
  * Rotate VALUEs after each request for a fair IP distribution.

